📄 StreamsCheatSheet.java — Comprehensive Reference (11 sections)
Filter, Map, Collect — basics on user-defined Employee objects
Sorting — single-field, multi-field, reversed, case-insensitive, by name length
Reduce & Aggregate — sum, avg, min, max, count, summaryStatistics(), custom reduce
Grouping & Partitioning — groupingBy with counting/averaging/mapping/maxBy, partitioningBy, custom buckets
FlatMap — nested collections (employee skills), skill frequency, flattening arrays
Collecting to Map — toMap, merge functions for duplicates, TreeMap, LinkedHashMap for ordering
Distinct, Limit, Skip, TakeWhile, DropWhile — pagination pattern, top-K
Find & Match — findFirst, findAny, anyMatch, allMatch, noneMatch
String Joining — Collectors.joining with delimiters, prefix, suffix
Complex Pipelines — 10 interview-style problems (2nd highest salary, top spender, dept analysis, Nth highest, etc.)
Streams on Maps — filter/sort/transform map entries, swap keys/values, merge maps, word frequency, character frequency
📄 StreamsQuickRef.java — Quick Copy-Paste Patterns (14 patterns)
Frequency maps, top-K, dedup, index-based ops, Fibonacci generation, palindrome check, string reversal, Collectors.teeing, parallel streams, etc.
Both files use user-defined classes (Employee, Order) with realistic data — exactly the kind of problems you'll see on Coding Signal. Good luck! 🚀